Dialogue: 2,0:00:02.62,0:00:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,2011年11月
Dialogue: 1,0:00:02.62,0:00:04.34,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,In November of 2011,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:04.34,0:00:07.61,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,NBC热播情景喜剧《废柴联盟》的演职人员
Dialogue: 1,0:00:04.34,0:00:07.61,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,the cast and crew of NBC's hit sitcom Community
Dialogue: 2,0:00:07.61,0:00:11.63,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,发现他们的预算严重超支  且进度落后
Dialogue: 1,0:00:07.61,0:00:11.63,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,found themselves hopelessly over budget and behind schedule.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:11.63,0:00:14.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,创剧人丹哈萌的解决办法 ——
Dialogue: 1,0:00:11.63,0:00:14.20,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Creator Dan Harmon's solution?
Dialogue: 2,0:00:14.20,0:00:16.11,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,拍一个两集的特别篇
Dialogue: 1,0:00:14.20,0:00:16.11,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Create a two-part episode,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:16.11,0:00:22.07,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,两集使用完全相同的道具  布景和服装
Dialogue: 1,0:00:16.11,0:00:22.07,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,the second part using all the same props, sets, and costumes as the previous.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:23.40,0:00:28.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们将面临电视网历史上一项前所未有的挑战
Dialogue: 1,0:00:23.40,0:00:28.48,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Together they would face one of the biggest challenges ever faced in network television history,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.48,0:00:35.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,编一部长篇战争纪录片风格的喜剧
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.48,0:00:35.00,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,writing comedy in the style of a really, really long documentary about war.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:35.00,0:00:38.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们从一开始就知道他们肩负的风险
Dialogue: 1,0:00:35.00,0:00:38.36,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,They knew at the outset the risks they were taking,
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.36,0:00:40.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但他们不在乎
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.36,0:00:40.06,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,but they didn't care.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:41.31,0:00:42.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以下是他们的故事
Dialogue: 1,0:00:41.31,0:00:42.60,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,This is their story.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:43.28,0:00:47.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,你好  我是切维·切斯
Dialogue: 1,0:00:43.28,0:00:47.28,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Hello, I'm Chevy Chase.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:47.28,0:00:51.37,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这里大部分的工作都有我的功劳
Dialogue: 1,0:00:47.28,0:00:51.37,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Most of what's going on around here has to do with me.
Dialogue: 2,0:00:58.88,0:01:01.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这种风格很容易模仿
Dialogue: 1,0:00:58.88,0:01:01.32,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,The style is very easy to emulate.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:01.32,0:01:06.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,现在我们经常看到纪录片在无休止地模仿这种风格
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.32,0:01:06.32,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It's something that we see all the time now, imitated by documentaries endlessly.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:06.32,0:01:10.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这集包含了很多静止的照片和大段旁白
Dialogue: 1,0:01:06.32,0:01:10.00,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It involves a lot of still photographs and narration and kind of a moving
Dialogue: 2,0:01:10.00,0:01:13.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,通过静景之上的镜头运动叙事
Dialogue: 1,0:01:10.00,0:01:13.44,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,camera on still photographs to kind of narrate the story.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:14.12,0:01:16.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,叙事方式包括  画外音
Dialogue: 1,0:01:14.12,0:01:16.72,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,The story being told through someone else's voice,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:16.72,0:01:18.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,一些真人动作和慢动作镜头
Dialogue: 1,0:01:16.72,0:01:18.80,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,some live action, some slow motion
Dialogue: 2,0:01:18.80,0:01:20.66,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,以及大量静景和访谈
Dialogue: 1,0:01:18.80,0:01:20.66,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and a lot of stills and talking heads.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:20.66,0:01:22.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,开始读剧本时  读到静景
Dialogue: 1,0:01:20.66,0:01:22.50,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,When you start reading, you're like, stills,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:22.50,0:01:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,会感到一头雾水
Dialogue: 1,0:01:22.50,0:01:24.50,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,I'm not quite sure what's happening.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.07,0:01:28.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,然后当了解到  要呈现这场类似内战的场景时
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.07,0:01:28.36,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,And then the idea that they were just going to do this whole sort of civil war,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:28.36,0:01:31.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,会感觉很酷  因为要重现之前拍摄的场景
Dialogue: 1,0:01:28.36,0:01:31.95,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,it just felt really cool because you were recreating these scenes that you shot,
Dialogue: 2,0:01:31.95,0:01:34.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但是要用手机来拍
Dialogue: 1,0:01:31.95,0:01:34.82,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,but now it's cell phone footage
Dialogue: 2,0:01:34.82,0:01:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,再加上
Dialogue: 1,0:01:34.82,0:01:37.33,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,and you know, uh...
Dialogue: 2,0:01:37.33,0:01:39.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,被布雷塔拍得很烂的照片
Dialogue: 1,0:01:37.33,0:01:39.70,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Britta's terrible picture she's taking.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:45.32,0:01:46.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我昨天演了我的第一段自白
Dialogue: 1,0:01:45.32,0:01:46.84,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I had my first confessional yesterday and
Dialogue: 2,0:01:46.84,0:01:48.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我不知道是该搞笑
Dialogue: 1,0:01:46.84,0:01:48.74,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,, I didn't know, is it supposed to be funny?
Dialogue: 2,0:01:48.74,0:01:50.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,还是该严肃
Dialogue: 1,0:01:48.74,0:01:50.26,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Is it supposed to be serious?
Dialogue: 2,0:01:50.26,0:01:53.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们说  这可是战争  伊薇特
Dialogue: 1,0:01:50.26,0:01:53.12,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,And they were like, this is war, Yvette.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.12,0:01:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你在战争中会有什么感受
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.12,0:01:55.72,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,How would you feel in a war?
Dialogue: 2,0:01:55.72,0:01:58.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我说  那可就非同一般了  我会非常严肃的
Dialogue: 1,0:01:55.72,0:01:58.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,And I said, well, that changes everything, I'd be very serious.
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.54,0:02:02.09,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这集的准备工作有所不同  因为我们的台词不多
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.54,0:02:02.09,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It's kind of a different type of preparation because we don't have as many lines,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:02.09,0:02:04.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,重点更多在于角色的态度和心理状态
Dialogue: 1,0:02:02.09,0:02:04.54,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,it's more like the attitude and what's going on with the characters
Dialogue: 2,0:02:04.54,0:02:05.86,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,整体氛围也更加严肃
Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.54,0:02:05.86,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and it's much more serious,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:05.86,0:02:07.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,感觉更加地...
Dialogue: 1,0:02:05.86,0:02:07.46,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,it kind of seems like a more...
Dialogue: 2,0:02:07.46,0:02:09.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们需要营造许多特别的瞬间
Dialogue: 1,0:02:07.46,0:02:09.43,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We had to create a bunch of moments,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:09.43,0:02:12.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,就很随性地进入场景
Dialogue: 1,0:02:09.43,0:02:12.38,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,it's just like coming in and just like
Dialogue: 2,0:02:12.38,0:02:16.15,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为所有的拍摄都是手持的  或者使用手机之类的设备
Dialogue: 1,0:02:12.38,0:02:16.15,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,cuz it's supposed to, like all the stuff is handheld and stuff or on phones and stuff like that,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:16.15,0:02:19.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,所以很多地方需要营造出一种即兴感
Dialogue: 1,0:02:16.15,0:02:19.80,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,so it's a lot of like making it feel like it's impromptu.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:19.80,0:02:25.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们用常规电影摄影机进行了整个战斗场面的拍摄
Dialogue: 1,0:02:19.80,0:02:25.06,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We did the whole battle with regular motion picture cameras,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:25.06,0:02:26.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且还用了数码相机
Dialogue: 1,0:02:25.06,0:02:26.74,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,or they're all digital cameras now.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.74,0:02:30.98,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们先把所有对话拍一遍  再用相机重现一遍
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.74,0:02:30.98,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,So we did all the dialogue we did for that and then we kind of staged the same thing,
Dialogue: 2,0:02:30.98,0:02:35.39,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,用的好像是佳能5D相机
Dialogue: 1,0:02:30.98,0:02:35.39,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,but they were just using a... I think Canon 5D camera
Dialogue: 2,0:02:35.39,0:02:38.77,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但只抓拍了剧本中描述的几个瞬间
Dialogue: 1,0:02:35.39,0:02:38.77,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,to just capture a couple of moments that are described in the script.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:38.77,0:02:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,导演快崩溃了
Dialogue: 1,0:02:38.77,0:02:41.04,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,And the director lost his mind
Dialogue: 2,0:02:41.04,0:02:45.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为要布置这些相当复杂的照片场景
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.04,0:02:45.94,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,because he had to stage these fairly intricate photographs.
Dialogue: 2,0:02:45.94,0:02:50.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,编剧可以很淡定地说  你通常每秒拍30帧
Dialogue: 1,0:02:45.94,0:02:50.74,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It was easy enough for the writers to say, you usually shoot 30 frames per second, so
Dialogue: 2,0:02:50.74,0:02:54.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,现在只要拍一帧  我觉得应该简单30倍  对吧
Dialogue: 1,0:02:50.74,0:02:54.42,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,this is just one frame for, I mean, it should be 30 times easier, right?
Dialogue: 2,0:02:54.42,0:02:59.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,至少有70张照片要拍  再加上地图的镜头
Dialogue: 1,0:02:54.42,0:02:59.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,There's at least 70 still photographs to take and we've got map footage and
Dialogue: 2,0:02:59.54,0:03:01.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这会很精彩
Dialogue: 1,0:02:59.54,0:03:01.02,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,it's gonna be fantastic.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.02,0:03:03.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我讨厌静景
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.02,0:03:03.58,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I hate still.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:03.58,0:03:06.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我在静景镜头里很丑
Dialogue: 1,0:03:03.58,0:03:06.58,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I just look terrible in still shots.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:06.58,0:03:09.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我甚至不喜欢照镜子  除非是刮胡子
Dialogue: 1,0:03:06.58,0:03:09.74,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I don't even like to look in the mirror except to shave.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:09.74,0:03:13.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如果那些照片是在动景中拍的
Dialogue: 1,0:03:09.74,0:03:13.72,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,If those shots are taken in the midst of motion
Dialogue: 2,0:03:13.72,0:03:16.28,Default,,0,0,0,,并且我没察觉到  那就行
Dialogue: 1,0:03:13.72,0:03:16.28,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,and I don't know about it, that's great.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:16.28,0:03:19.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如果要我凹造型  呃  我讨厌这样
Dialogue: 1,0:03:16.28,0:03:19.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,If I have to pose, I, ugh, I hate it.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:25.54,0:03:31.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我想在这一季中让他们的友谊更加立体
Dialogue: 1,0:03:25.54,0:03:31.12,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I wanted to dimensionalize their friendship this season,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:31.12,0:03:34.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,不是破坏他们的友谊  而是
Dialogue: 1,0:03:31.12,0:03:34.86,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,not by tarnishing it, but just
Dialogue: 2,0:03:34.86,0:03:39.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,通过展现一个真实版本的友谊
Dialogue: 1,0:03:34.86,0:03:39.86,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,by demonstrating that there was a real version
Dialogue: 2,0:03:39.86,0:03:43.18,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,让它看起来不那么卡通
Dialogue: 1,0:03:39.86,0:03:43.18,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,of what otherwise seemed sort of cartoony.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:43.18,0:03:46.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这对形影不离的死党
Dialogue: 1,0:03:43.18,0:03:46.72,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,These two best friends who seemed completely inseparable
Dialogue: 2,0:03:46.72,0:03:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,别人一直调侃他们的亲密关系
Dialogue: 1,0:03:46.72,0:03:48.52,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,and that being a joke for so long.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:48.52,0:03:52.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,特洛伊和阿布蒂  他们意气相投
Dialogue: 1,0:03:48.52,0:03:52.14,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,Troy and Abed, they never don't like each other,
Dialogue: 2,0:03:52.14,0:03:54.90,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,他们一体同心
Dialogue: 1,0:03:52.14,0:03:54.90,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,they never don't think the same thing.
Dialogue: 2,0:03:54.90,0:04:01.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我想用一种更贴近现实的社交视角来审视这一季
Dialogue: 1,0:03:54.90,0:04:01.26,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I wanted to look at it this season through a lens of slightly more realistic social dynamics
Dialogue: 2,0:04:01.26,0:04:04.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,特别强调了阿布蒂这个角色
Dialogue: 1,0:04:01.26,0:04:04.58,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,with an emphasis on the idea that Abed is a character
Dialogue: 2,0:04:04.58,0:04:07.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,与特洛伊在本质上的不同
Dialogue: 1,0:04:04.58,0:04:07.32,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,who is different from Troy in a fundamental way.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:07.51,0:04:10.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这是本剧的一个关键时刻
Dialogue: 1,0:04:07.51,0:04:10.46,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,It's a nice monumental turning point for the show
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.46,0:04:11.95,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,他们的友谊
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.46,0:04:11.95,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,where their friendship is
Dialogue: 2,0:04:11.95,0:04:15.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,将面临一种只有他们才能经历的独特考验
Dialogue: 1,0:04:11.95,0:04:15.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,tested in a way that only Troy and Abed can test their friendship.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.54,0:04:18.02,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)}你应该把小的放在中间  不然墙撑不住天花板
Dialogue: 2,0:04:18.02,0:04:20.54,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,为啥总是我来当你的雷吉
Dialogue: 2,0:04:20.54,0:04:21.54,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,你想说啥
Dialogue: 2,0:04:21.54,0:04:24.22,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,我想建一个毯子城堡  这事你想都没想过
Dialogue: 2,0:04:24.91,0:04:26.82,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,我连你的副手都算不上  就是个小跟班
Dialogue: 2,0:04:26.82,0:04:28.06,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,我没不让你干什么啊
Dialogue: 2,0:04:28.86,0:04:30.86,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,你要是想建毯子城堡  我没意见
Dialogue: 2,0:04:31.86,0:04:32.86,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,谢谢
Dialogue: 2,0:04:32.86,0:04:34.70,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,只要别和我的枕头堡沾边
Dialogue: 2,0:04:34.70,0:04:39.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,刚开始  我对丹哈萌有点表示怀疑
Dialogue: 1,0:04:34.70,0:04:39.36,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Early on, I was sort of gently pushing back to Dan Harmon saying like,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:39.36,0:04:43.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,开玩笑吗  在NBC周四晚八点的黄金档
Dialogue: 1,0:04:39.36,0:04:43.14,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,really for on a Thursday night, eight o'clock on NBC,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:43.14,0:04:45.31,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,在电视上这样玩
Dialogue: 1,0:04:43.14,0:04:45.31,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,like on network television we're gonna do this
Dialogue: 2,0:04:45.31,0:04:48.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这难道不是大家经常批评的
Dialogue: 1,0:04:45.31,0:04:48.38,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,And isn't this what people complain about,
Dialogue: 2,0:04:48.38,0:04:50.84,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,觉得我们的剧太另类  太高冷吗
Dialogue: 1,0:04:48.38,0:04:50.84,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,that we're too weird and that the inaccessible
Dialogue: 2,0:04:50.84,0:04:55.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但他坚持说  正因如此  我们才必须这么做
Dialogue: 1,0:04:50.84,0:04:55.58,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and he kept saying, that's why we have to do it.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:55.58,0:04:57.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他一直强调  这绝对行得通
Dialogue: 1,0:04:55.58,0:04:57.84,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,He kept saying, no, it'll work.
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.84,0:05:01.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,最棘手的挑战在于第二集的创作
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.84,0:05:01.88,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,The biggest challenge was in the writing of the second episode
Dialogue: 2,0:05:01.88,0:05:05.38,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为需要堆砌词藻
Dialogue: 1,0:05:01.88,0:05:05.38,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,because you have to get very wordy.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:05.38,0:05:08.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们尝试去模拟一种风格
Dialogue: 1,0:05:05.38,0:05:08.06,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,You're trying to emulate a style
Dialogue: 2,0:05:08.06,0:05:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,这通常是以戏剧性而非喜剧性的方式呈现
Dialogue: 1,0:05:08.06,0:05:12.94,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,that is usually rolled out, not only dramatically as opposed to communically
Dialogue: 2,0:05:12.94,0:05:15.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且需要3小时甚至更长时间来展开
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.94,0:05:15.40,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,but in three hours or more.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:15.40,0:05:18.95,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我想  我们在制作过程中经常会相视而笑
Dialogue: 1,0:05:15.40,0:05:18.95,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,And I think we're finding, we've had plenty of moments when we were making this and
Dialogue: 2,0:05:18.95,0:05:23.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,心里暗自得意地想着  没错  没错  是这样
Dialogue: 1,0:05:18.95,0:05:23.52,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,we thought that we kind of smiled devilishly to each other thinking like, yeah, yeah, yeah,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:23.52,0:05:24.67,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这个真的会很棒
Dialogue: 1,0:05:23.52,0:05:24.67,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I think this is going to be great.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:31.48,0:05:34.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们在第二季搭过一个毯子城堡
Dialogue: 1,0:05:31.48,0:05:34.26,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,We had done a blanket fort episode on season two,
Dialogue: 2,0:05:34.26,0:05:36.76,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,所以我们对此有一定经验
Dialogue: 1,0:05:34.26,0:05:36.76,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,so we kind of knew what was going on but
Dialogue: 2,0:05:36.76,0:05:40.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但枕头堡的搭建就更加复杂了
Dialogue: 1,0:05:36.76,0:05:40.08,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,with the pillow fort, it's a little more complicated
Dialogue: 2,0:05:40.08,0:05:44.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毕竟  考虑到阿布蒂的个性  他会把每个细节做到极致
Dialogue: 1,0:05:40.08,0:05:44.56,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,because, of course being who Abed is would do like this perfect job
Dialogue: 2,0:05:44.56,0:05:47.54,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,确保一切在理论上精准无误
Dialogue: 1,0:05:44.56,0:05:47.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and make sure everything is mathematically correct
Dialogue: 2,0:05:47.54,0:05:50.42,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并保持美观上的协调
Dialogue: 1,0:05:47.54,0:05:50.42,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,and aesthetically the kind of the same.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:50.42,0:05:54.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们从本剧片头的折纸游戏这种小点子出发
Dialogue: 1,0:05:50.42,0:05:54.10,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We've taken the idea of something like the cootie catcher, which is the beginning of the show
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.10,0:05:57.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,进一步深化这个概念
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.10,0:05:57.12,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and you know, extrapolated the idea.
Dialogue: 2,0:05:57.12,0:06:01.13,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,当我们读到网格球顶的部分时  都在想  哇
Dialogue: 1,0:05:57.12,0:06:01.13,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We read the geodesic dome and that was something we thought, oh, gee,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:01.13,0:06:02.84,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这怎么可能实现呢
Dialogue: 1,0:06:01.13,0:06:02.84,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,how is that going to happen, but
Dialogue: 2,0:06:02.84,0:06:06.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,好在我们的搭景协调员约翰·理查森  找来了个
Dialogue: 1,0:06:02.84,0:06:06.76,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,But our construction coordinator, John Richardson, found a...
Dialogue: 2,0:06:06.76,0:06:09.79,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,火人节上别人用过的网格球顶
Dialogue: 1,0:06:06.76,0:06:09.79,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,a geodesic dome that someone had from Burning Man
Dialogue: 2,0:06:09.79,0:06:12.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,而且价格非常合理
Dialogue: 1,0:06:09.79,0:06:12.10,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,and it was like really inexpensive,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:12.10,0:06:14.36,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,比我们自己从头开始建造要便宜得多
Dialogue: 1,0:06:12.10,0:06:14.36,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,you know, compared to having to build everything.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:14.36,0:06:16.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们还特别注意颜色上的差异
Dialogue: 1,0:06:14.36,0:06:16.72,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We also wanted to color differentiations.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:16.72,0:06:19.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们寻求具有质感的面料
Dialogue: 1,0:06:16.72,0:06:19.92,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,We tried to shop fabrics that were textural
Dialogue: 2,0:06:19.92,0:06:22.40,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,所以使用了大量的灯芯绒
Dialogue: 1,0:06:19.92,0:06:22.40,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,so that there's a lot of corduroy in the set.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:22.40,0:06:26.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,初次采购就像一场寻宝  要找到能体现角色个性的物品
Dialogue: 1,0:06:22.40,0:06:26.32,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It was like the first shopping trip was to find things that were, that spoke to the characters
Dialogue: 2,0:06:26.32,0:06:31.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我还有相当一部分工作  为角色挑选适合的颜色
Dialogue: 1,0:06:26.32,0:06:31.06,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and a lot of what I was doing was also finding the colors that I thought they'd look good in.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:31.06,0:06:35.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们真应该对我们的美术组表示赞赏
Dialogue: 1,0:06:31.06,0:06:35.10,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We should compliment like the art department here because they are incredible.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:35.10,0:06:37.72,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们搭建的枕头和毯子城堡非常出色
Dialogue: 1,0:06:35.10,0:06:37.72,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,And like building the pillows and the blanket forts.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:37.72,0:06:41.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,枕头堡令人赞叹  我真希望我家里也有一个
Dialogue: 1,0:06:37.72,0:06:41.70,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Like the pillow fort is by far like, I wish that was in my house, like it's so,
Dialogue: 2,0:06:41.70,0:06:45.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,它不仅复杂精致而且非常酷  你甚至可以在里面爬行
Dialogue: 1,0:06:41.70,0:06:45.40,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,it's so intricate and really cool and like you can crawl through it.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:45.40,0:06:47.32,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这不是胡说八道  也不是电脑特效
Dialogue: 1,0:06:45.40,0:06:47.32,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It's not like, it's not bulls, it's not computers.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:47.32,0:06:48.48,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我不清楚别人怎么想的
Dialogue: 1,0:06:47.32,0:06:48.48,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I don't know what people think.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:48.48,0:06:51.44,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我亲眼见证了它的建造过程  很壮观
Dialogue: 1,0:06:48.48,0:06:51.44,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I saw it being built and I thought this is spectacular.
Dialogue: 2,0:06:51.44,0:06:56.73,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,每次想到我们居然能在毯枕堡里拍摄  我都很震惊
Dialogue: 1,0:06:51.44,0:06:56.73,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It's always so amazing to me that we're actually able to shoot in the blanket fort, in the pillow fort
Dialogue: 2,0:06:56.73,0:06:59.33,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为它们外表看起来很小
Dialogue: 1,0:06:56.73,0:06:59.33,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,cuz it looks so small from the outside and
Dialogue: 2,0:06:59.33,0:07:03.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们竟能把摄影机  灯光  演员  收音这一切都安置好
Dialogue: 1,0:06:59.33,0:07:03.64,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,the fact that they can get cameras and lights and actors and sound and everything in there
Dialogue: 2,0:07:03.64,0:07:05.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这让我印象深刻
Dialogue: 1,0:07:03.64,0:07:05.36,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,is always so impressive to me.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:05.36,0:07:09.64,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这种情况每周都会发生  但这次他们拆学校的原因是
Dialogue: 1,0:07:05.36,0:07:09.64,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,And they do this every week on the show, but they once again had to destroy the campus
Dialogue: 2,0:07:09.64,0:07:12.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,玩枕头大战
Dialogue: 1,0:07:09.64,0:07:12.04,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,this time in a pillow fight.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:12.04,0:07:13.60,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,搞得满地羽毛
Dialogue: 1,0:07:12.04,0:07:13.60,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,So there's feathers everywhere.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:13.60,0:07:18.02,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们建造了这个巨型枕头堡
Dialogue: 1,0:07:13.60,0:07:18.02,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,They created these massive pillow forts that
Dialogue: 2,0:07:18.02,0:07:22.20,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,并按照剧本中要求的那样  看起来构造精巧
Dialogue: 1,0:07:18.02,0:07:22.20,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,we said in the script, need to look like they're architecturally sophisticated
Dialogue: 2,0:07:22.20,0:07:23.20,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,他们真的做到了
Dialogue: 1,0:07:22.20,0:07:23.20,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and they did.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:24.64,0:07:25.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这太不可思议了
Dialogue: 1,0:07:24.64,0:07:25.92,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It's insane.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:25.92,0:07:30.12,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,枕头堡是由每块2x4英尺的部分组成的
Dialogue: 1,0:07:25.92,0:07:30.12,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,The pillow fort is constructed like in two by four foot sections.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:30.12,0:07:33.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们可以根据拍摄需求移开一些侧壁
Dialogue: 1,0:07:30.12,0:07:33.58,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,So we can wild out some of the walls as we need to
Dialogue: 2,0:07:33.58,0:07:35.36,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,也可以拆除一些天花板
Dialogue: 1,0:07:33.58,0:07:35.36,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and we can take off some of the ceilings
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.36,0:07:38.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,方便我们布置灯光
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.36,0:07:38.40,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,so they can throw light in and we have accessibility.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:38.40,0:07:42.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们还设置了一些独立的柱子和角落
Dialogue: 1,0:07:38.40,0:07:42.76,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,And we have like columns, freestanding columns and corners
Dialogue: 2,0:07:42.76,0:07:44.72,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,这样就可以调整这些部分
Dialogue: 1,0:07:42.76,0:07:44.72,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,so we can move those pieces around
Dialogue: 2,0:07:44.72,0:07:47.86,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,让它看起来像枕头堡的不同区域
Dialogue: 1,0:07:44.72,0:07:47.86,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,so it looks like we're in a different part of the pillow fort.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:47.86,0:07:51.50,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我一直都觉得  我们的美术和道具组做事非常认真细致
Dialogue: 1,0:07:47.86,0:07:51.50,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I've always said this, our art department and our prop department are so thorough.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:51.50,0:07:56.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们在有限的预算下做出了令人惊叹的布景和道具
Dialogue: 1,0:07:51.50,0:07:56.36,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,They create amazing sets and props and whatever like on a dime.
Dialogue: 2,0:07:56.36,0:08:01.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,剧本可能会突然要求  需要一个完全用枕头装扮的角色
Dialogue: 1,0:07:56.36,0:08:01.45,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We literally will get pages and it's like oh so we need to have someone dressed in pillows completely
Dialogue: 2,0:08:01.45,0:08:03.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,服装道具组的所有人都会立刻行动起来
Dialogue: 1,0:08:01.45,0:08:03.53,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and the word department and the props and everybody's going to say
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.53,0:08:05.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们会各司其职
Dialogue: 1,0:08:03.53,0:08:05.45,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,okay we're going to do this and I'm going to bring this in and
Dialogue: 2,0:08:05.45,0:08:08.80,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,这真是一个由极具创造力的人组成的团队
Dialogue: 1,0:08:05.45,0:08:08.80,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,it's like a great group of people that really are creative
Dialogue: 2,0:08:08.80,0:08:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,他们能迅速应对各种突发状况
Dialogue: 1,0:08:08.80,0:08:11.58,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,and can do anything at the drop of a dime.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:16.94,0:08:20.30,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在皮尔斯的想象中  他一定是最出色的战士
Dialogue: 1,0:08:16.94,0:08:20.30,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I think in Pierce's mind he would be the finest soldier.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:20.30,0:08:21.90,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)}你能造出来吗
Dialogue: 2,0:08:21.90,0:08:24.22,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,你得给我提供枕头
Dialogue: 2,0:08:24.22,0:08:26.66,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,希望我们永远也不会用上它
Dialogue: 2,0:08:26.66,0:08:27.66,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,我也这么想
Dialogue: 2,0:08:27.66,0:08:31.88,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,杰夫绝不愿意弄乱他的发型
Dialogue: 1,0:08:27.66,0:08:31.88,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Hey we'll hurry cause Jeff didn't want his hair to get messed up.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:31.88,0:08:35.76,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他不可能穿睡衣  但会穿那种有点行动不便的衣服
Dialogue: 1,0:08:31.88,0:08:35.76,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,He's not gonna be wearing pajamas so he might be wearing something that's hindering him a little bit
Dialogue: 2,0:08:35.76,0:08:37.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他只要风度不要温度
Dialogue: 1,0:08:35.76,0:08:37.82,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,but he will sacrifice anything for fashion.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:37.82,0:08:39.16,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我选伦纳德
Dialogue: 1,0:08:37.82,0:08:39.16,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I'm gonna go with Leonard.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:39.80,0:08:40.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,雪莉很厉害
Dialogue: 1,0:08:39.80,0:08:40.56,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Shirley's pretty good.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:40.56,0:08:41.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,雪莉很勇猛
Dialogue: 1,0:08:40.56,0:08:41.56,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Shirley's really good.
