Dialogue: 1,0:08:41.56,0:08:42.37,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:42.37,0:08:45.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,就像在剧集中看到的那样  她似乎有点战争狂的倾向
Dialogue: 1,0:08:42.37,0:08:45.74,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I mean she's got, I mean like we've seen in other episodes that she's kind of like a war monger.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:45.74,0:08:49.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,是的  她似乎总是在等待这些混乱的时刻  你突然会发现
Dialogue: 1,0:08:45.74,0:08:49.14,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Yeah she kind of waits for these moments where there's chaos and all of a sudden you're like
Dialogue: 2,0:08:49.14,0:08:51.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,好吧  原来她这么能打
Dialogue: 1,0:08:49.14,0:08:51.47,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,oh okay you are good at battle.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:54.32,0:08:57.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,雪莉显然非常骁勇善战
Dialogue: 1,0:08:54.32,0:08:57.46,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Shirley apparently is very good in combat.
Dialogue: 2,0:08:57.46,0:09:01.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们在两次彩弹大战集就发现了这一点
Dialogue: 1,0:08:57.46,0:09:01.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We found that out in the first paintball episode, the second paintball episode
Dialogue: 2,0:09:01.54,0:09:05.53,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这已经是在格林戴尔校园发生的第三次大战
Dialogue: 1,0:09:01.54,0:09:05.53,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and now this is the third epic battle that has taken place on Greendale's campus and
Dialogue: 2,0:09:05.53,0:09:10.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,雪莉在必要时能够彻底击溃敌人
Dialogue: 1,0:09:05.53,0:09:10.74,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Shirley really rises up and destroys human beings when she needs to.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:10.74,0:09:12.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我非常擅长被动进攻
Dialogue: 1,0:09:10.74,0:09:12.45,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I'm a very passive aggressive fighter.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:14.72,0:09:15.92,Line-zh,,0,0,0,,打中了  好了我挂了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:17.54,0:09:19.26,Line-zh,,0,0,0,,别打了  我挂了
Dialogue: 2,0:09:19.96,0:09:22.62,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我是最会耍手段的战士
Dialogue: 1,0:09:19.96,0:09:22.62,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I'm the dirtiest fighter in the game.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:22.62,0:09:25.94,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我私认为是  院长
Dialogue: 1,0:09:22.62,0:09:25.94,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,I think I'm selfishly going to just say the Dean
Dialogue: 2,0:09:25.94,0:09:28.70,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为如果他加入到学习小组的枕头大战中
Dialogue: 1,0:09:25.94,0:09:28.70,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,only cuz if he got into a pillow fight with the study group
Dialogue: 2,0:09:28.70,0:09:33.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他可能会忙着乱摸  其他人就被吓跑了
Dialogue: 1,0:09:28.70,0:09:33.40,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,he'd probably just do a lot of groping, they'd want to leave.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:33.40,0:09:35.62,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们小组里的每个成员都很机智
Dialogue: 1,0:09:33.40,0:09:35.62,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Everybody's pretty crafty in our group.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:35.62,0:09:37.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我觉得不能轻视任何一个人
Dialogue: 1,0:09:35.62,0:09:37.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I don't think you could count anyone out
Dialogue: 2,0:09:37.54,0:09:40.35,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为他们通常都有备而来  并暗藏杀机
Dialogue: 1,0:09:37.54,0:09:40.35,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,because they usually have a couple of tricks up their sleeve.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:40.35,0:09:43.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我们是一群没有道德底线  冷酷无情的人
Dialogue: 1,0:09:40.35,0:09:43.57,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,We're a bunch of amoral ruthless people so
Dialogue: 2,0:09:43.57,0:09:47.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这将是一场持续到底的七方角逐
Dialogue: 1,0:09:43.57,0:09:47.56,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,it'd be a seven-way battle to the end.
Dialogue: 2,0:09:52.45,0:09:54.34,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毯子还是枕头
Dialogue: 1,0:09:52.45,0:09:54.34,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Blanket or pillow person?
Dialogue: 2,0:09:54.34,0:09:57.92,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,枕头很舒服  很可爱  很柔软
Dialogue: 1,0:09:54.34,0:09:57.92,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Pillows are comfortable and cuddly and soft
Dialogue: 2,0:09:57.92,0:09:59.91,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毯子提供温暖
Dialogue: 1,0:09:57.92,0:09:59.91,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and blankets provide warmth.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:00.32,0:10:01.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毯子
Dialogue: 1,0:10:00.32,0:10:01.40,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Blanket.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:02.02,0:10:02.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毯子
Dialogue: 1,0:10:02.02,0:10:02.56,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Blanket.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:02.56,0:10:03.62,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,谁会选枕头呢
Dialogue: 1,0:10:02.56,0:10:03.62,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Who would choose this pillow?
Dialogue: 2,0:10:03.62,0:10:06.00,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我猜丹尼会选择枕头
Dialogue: 1,0:10:03.62,0:10:06.00,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I think Danny's gonna choose pillow.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:06.00,0:10:08.14,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我大概会选枕头
Dialogue: 1,0:10:06.00,0:10:08.14,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I would probably have to go with pillow.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:08.14,0:10:12.18,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比起温暖我更喜欢柔软  所以我选择枕头
Dialogue: 1,0:10:08.14,0:10:12.18,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I think I prefer softness to heat so I'm going pillows.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:12.84,0:10:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,不对
Dialogue: 1,0:10:12.84,0:10:13.94,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:15.51,0:10:19.59,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我选毯子  因为毯子可以卷起来当枕头用
Dialogue: 1,0:10:15.51,0:10:19.59,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I'd go with blanket I think because blankets can be rolled into pillows.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:19.59,0:10:21.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,枕套里还能存放东西
Dialogue: 1,0:10:19.59,0:10:21.74,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,You could store stuff in a pillowcase.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:22.68,0:10:25.82,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,比如在末日时刻  你可以在里面装东西  方便携带
Dialogue: 1,0:10:22.68,0:10:25.82,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Like if there's the apocalypse you could put stuff in there and you can carry it.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:25.82,0:10:28.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我可以不用枕头
Dialogue: 1,0:10:25.82,0:10:28.40,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,I can do without a pillow you know
Dialogue: 2,0:10:28.40,0:10:30.95,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,我喜欢毯子  它晚上能给我温暖
Dialogue: 1,0:10:28.40,0:10:30.95,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I like blankets, it keeps me warm at night.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:30.95,0:10:33.06,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毯子无疑
Dialogue: 1,0:10:30.95,0:10:33.06,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Blanket. Easily.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:33.06,0:10:38.08,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我想说  任何东西都能变成枕头
Dialogue: 1,0:10:33.06,0:10:38.08,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I mean I think, I think you can make anything into a pillow but
Dialogue: 2,0:10:38.08,0:10:40.57,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但毯子的温度是无可替代的
Dialogue: 1,0:10:38.08,0:10:40.57,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,the warmth of a blanket you cannot replicate.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:40.57,0:10:41.55,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毯子
Dialogue: 1,0:10:40.57,0:10:41.55,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Blanket.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:42.25,0:10:43.25,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,毫无疑问
Dialogue: 1,0:10:42.25,0:10:43.25,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Absolutely.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:44.62,0:10:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,毯子可以覆盖整个身体
Dialogue: 1,0:10:44.62,0:10:46.50,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,It covers your whole body.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:46.50,0:10:50.43,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,如果需要枕头  只要把毯子卷起来就行了
Dialogue: 1,0:10:46.50,0:10:50.43,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,You know if you need a pillow you just roll it up and you got a pillow.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:50.43,0:10:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以用毯子把自己卷起来
Dialogue: 1,0:10:50.43,0:10:53.00,Default-L2,,0,0,0,,And you can surround yourself
Dialogue: 2,0:10:53.00,0:10:56.46,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,创造一个舒适温馨的小空间
Dialogue: 1,0:10:53.00,0:10:56.46,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and make it into a wonderful little cozy space for you
Dialogue: 2,0:10:56.46,0:10:59.04,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,因为枕头可以放在任何地方
Dialogue: 1,0:10:56.46,0:10:59.04,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,because pillows they can go anywhere.
Dialogue: 2,0:10:59.04,0:11:02.24,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这很疯狂  甚至可能携带疾病
Dialogue: 1,0:10:59.04,0:11:02.24,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It's pretty crazy and they carry disease.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:02.24,0:11:04.33,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我觉得自己可能在两边都能找到归属感
Dialogue: 1,0:11:02.24,0:11:04.33,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I could see myself on either side
Dialogue: 2,0:11:04.33,0:11:08.90,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我欣赏阿布蒂对细节的专注和他的完美主义
Dialogue: 1,0:11:04.33,0:11:08.90,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I appreciate Abed's attention to detail and his perfectionism
Dialogue: 2,0:11:08.90,0:11:14.54,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,同时我也喜欢特洛伊的娱乐精神和他的随和天性
Dialogue: 1,0:11:08.90,0:11:14.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and then I like Troy's spirit of fun and his sort of easygoing nature so
Dialogue: 2,0:11:14.54,0:11:17.21,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,所以我两边都有点倾向  能这样说吗
Dialogue: 1,0:11:14.54,0:11:17.21,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,So, a little bit of both. How about that?
Dialogue: 2,0:11:17.21,0:11:21.58,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我更倾向于舒适自在的东西
Dialogue: 1,0:11:17.21,0:11:21.58,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I'm more of a like a a snuggie kind of person.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:23.01,0:11:26.22,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我认为这一集绝对是天才之作  因为这正是本剧的特色
Dialogue: 1,0:11:23.01,0:11:26.22,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,No I thought this is going to be a genius episode because this is what this show does.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:26.22,0:11:30.26,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,这集将传统的情景喜剧格式彻底颠覆
Dialogue: 1,0:11:26.22,0:11:30.26,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,It takes a traditional situation comedy kind of format and just turns it on its head
Dialogue: 2,0:11:30.26,0:11:31.54,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我觉得这非常棒
Dialogue: 1,0:11:30.26,0:11:31.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and I just think that's great.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:31.54,0:11:36.56,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我觉得这集非常大胆  再一次打破常规
Dialogue: 1,0:11:31.54,0:11:36.56,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I thought it was so adventurous and so pushing the envelope yet again
Dialogue: 2,0:11:36.56,0:11:41.74,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,去拍一部关于这场枕毯堡战争的纪录片
Dialogue: 1,0:11:36.56,0:11:41.74,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,to do a documentary about this epic pillow fort blanket fort war.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:41.74,0:11:46.34,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,对我来说  最精彩的部分是看布雷塔拍那些拙劣的照片
Dialogue: 1,0:11:41.74,0:11:46.34,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,The highlight for me was watching Britta taking inept photos
Dialogue: 2,0:11:46.34,0:11:50.45,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,布雷塔这个角色  真是个瑰宝
Dialogue: 1,0:11:46.34,0:11:50.45,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Britta, that character is just yeah she's a gem man.
Dialogue: 2,0:11:50.45,0:11:55.40,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,甚至昨天看着你们站在那儿  我都觉得很棒
Dialogue: 1,0:11:50.45,0:11:55.40,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,There's something so great even yesterday watching you guys stand there and you're like
Dialogue: 2,0:11:55.40,0:11:58.47,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,裹着毛毯和枕套  互相用枕头打闹
Dialogue: 1,0:11:55.40,0:11:58.47,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,wrapped in blankets and pillowcases hitting each other with pillows and I was like
Dialogue: 2,0:11:58.47,0:12:02.28,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,心想  这就是我们的工作  每周如此
Dialogue: 1,0:11:58.47,0:12:02.28,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,this is our job, this is pretty cool that like every week it is
Dialogue: 2,0:12:02.28,0:12:07.49,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,每周都在做不同的  傻气的  怪异的  不可思议的事情
Dialogue: 1,0:12:02.28,0:12:07.49,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,something different and silly and weird and incredible.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:07.49,0:12:11.80,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,我最喜欢的是上半部分的最后一幕  特洛伊和阿布蒂
Dialogue: 1,0:12:07.49,0:12:11.80,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I love the moment at the end it's when we see the slow-mo shots of Troy and Abed
Dialogue: 2,0:12:11.80,0:12:17.10,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,在慢镜头中相互凝视  试图抑制他们身后的混乱
Dialogue: 1,0:12:11.80,0:12:17.10,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,looking across the room at each other as they try to restrain the rabble behind them.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:17.10,0:12:24.52,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,唐纳德和丹尼这两位非常有趣的演员
Dialogue: 1,0:12:17.10,0:12:24.52,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,The depth that Donald Glover and Danny Pudi who guys who are so funny
Dialogue: 2,0:12:24.52,0:12:27.93,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,他们完全不需要深入挖掘
Dialogue: 1,0:12:24.52,0:12:27.93,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,they have no need to go that deep
Dialogue: 2,0:12:27.93,0:12:32.29,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,凭借他们的喜剧才能本可以轻松过关
Dialogue: 1,0:12:27.93,0:12:32.29,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,because they're funny enough to subsist purely on comedy chops.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:32.29,0:12:36.36,Default,atg1,0,0,0,,但他们还是为了展现本剧戏剧性的一面而煞费苦心
Dialogue: 1,0:12:32.29,0:12:36.36,Default-L2,atg1,0,0,0,,They bother to play Community for its dramatic points
Dialogue: 2,0:12:36.36,0:12:38.98,Default,atg7,0,0,0,,为了更好地传达剧情
Dialogue: 1,0:12:36.36,0:12:38.98,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,when necessary to tell the story.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:41.20,0:12:41.90,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,别看我
Dialogue: 1,0:12:41.20,0:12:41.90,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Don't look at me.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:41.90,0:12:43.99,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,我穿着睡衣
Dialogue: 1,0:12:41.90,0:12:43.99,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I'm wearing my pajamies
Dialogue: 2,0:12:43.99,0:12:46.28,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,因为我的肌肉紧绷
Dialogue: 1,0:12:43.99,0:12:46.28,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,cuz I got hammies that are tight.
Dialogue: 2,0:12:46.28,0:12:47.54,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,让它们放松
Dialogue: 1,0:12:46.28,0:12:47.54,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,Got to stretch them
Dialogue: 2,0:12:47.54,0:12:49.07,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,然后我会说晚安
Dialogue: 1,0:12:47.54,0:12:49.07,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,and then I'll say good night
Dialogue: 2,0:12:49.07,0:12:52.63,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,因为外面很黑  我累了  兄弟
Dialogue: 1,0:12:49.07,0:12:52.63,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,cuz it's dark out yo and I'm tired bro
Dialogue: 2,0:12:52.63,0:12:56.22,Line-zh,atg1,0,0,0,,我一整天都在打你  扔你
Dialogue: 1,0:12:52.63,0:12:56.22,Default-L2,atg7,0,0,0,,I've been up all day hitting you and throw
